<div><h3>PSYC 227 - Research on Addictive Behaviors </h3>  <p><hr>This course involves students participating in ongoing research examining the etiology and treatment of addictive behaviors. This includes research projects investigating risk factors for relapse to substance use and treatment development for substance-using populations. Students will become familiar with basic theories, research methods, and research findings in addictions; actively participate in research team meetings; and develop competence in key research tasks.</p>

<p>Prerequisites for this course require a grade of C- or better</p>

